==Notes==
{{Div col|small=yes|cols=2}}

*{{note label|Par|a|a}} Par is a predetermined number of strokes that a golfer should require to complete a hole, a round (the sum of the total pars of the played holes), or a tournament (the sum of the total pars of each round). E stands for even, which means the tournament was completed in the predetermined number of strokes.  The best score should always be the lowest in relation to par.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/golf/rules_and_equipment/4749181.stm |title=Scoring |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |accessdate=2008-09-23 | date=2005-09-16}}</ref>
*{{note label|Matchplay|b|b}} The first event was contested in [[match play]] competition.  This means the score is reported differently.<ref name=First />
*{{note label|Rawls|c|c}} Betsy Rawls won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Jackie Pung]], 70â77.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Cornelius|d|d}} Kathy Cornelius won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Barbara McIntire]] (a), 75â82.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Wright|e|e}} Mickey Wright won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Ruth Jessen]], 70â72.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Carner|f|f}} JoAnne Carner won in an 18-hole playoff over Sandra Palmer, 76â78.<ref name=USOPEN /> 
*{{note label|Geddes|g|g}} Jane Geddes won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Sally Little]], 71â73.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Davies|h|h}} Laura Davies won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Ayako Okamoto]] and JoAnne Carner, 71â73â74.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Sheehan|i|i}} Patty Sheehan won in an 18-hole playoff over Juli Inkster, 72â74.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Pak|j|j}} Se Ri Pak won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Jenny Chuasiriporn]] (a), 73â73, which she won in sudden death after that on the second extra hole.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Lunke|k|k}} Hilary Lunke won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Angela Stanford]] and [[Kelly Robbins]], 70â71â73.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Sorenstam|l|l}} Annika SÃ¶renstam won in an 18-hole playoff over [[Pat Hurst]], 70â74.<ref name=USOPEN />
*{{note label|Ryu|m|m}} So Yeon Ryu won won in a 3-hole playoff over [[Hee Kyung Seo]], 10â13.<ref name="2011 winner"/>
